     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <head>
      <hi>To Sir</hi> ROBERT GAVDY.</head>
   <l>FIrst, if I might safely craue this worlds pelfe;</l>
   <l>To be belou'd next would I wish my selfe,</l>
   <l>And rather then the first alone I'de chuse,</l>
   <l>The second I would take and that refuse.</l>
   <l>But you Sir <hi>Robert</hi> haue fates bl<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>ssing got,</l>
   <l>Y'are wealthy, and belou'd, yea and what not</l>
   <l>Nor euer were the Starres more iust (I swear't)</l>
   <l>With such great goods, to trust such good desert.</l>
</div>
